From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] gcc/expr: canonicalize POINTER_PLUS_EXPR offset under hybrid

POINTER_PLUS_EXPR expansion already handles the two precision-mismatch
cases (sizetype narrower / wider than pointer type) by inserting a
fold_convert that forces a sign-extending widen / truncate at RTL
emission.  When the precisions match, the original code falls straight
through to PLUS_EXPR expansion with no canonicalization.

On a target where Pmode is smaller than the natural machine word --
ELF64 + ILP32 hybrid on powerpc64-ps3-elf -- the subsequent PLUS_EXPR
lowers to a full-width hardware add (PPC `add` is always 64-bit).
The base pointer is canonical (zero-extended) but the offset coming
out of signed integer arithmetic may have non-canonical upper bits
(e.g. subf wrapping into negative leaves the upper 32 as 0xffffffff).
That noncanonical value propagates into the resulting effective
address and breaks subsequent memory access.  This was the
stb_truetype `data[(y-iy0)*w+(x-ix0)]` crash on `oss << int_value`
paths in EMP code.

Add a third branch to the precision-match case: when the pointer mode
is narrower than UNITS_PER_WORD, sign-widen the offset through a
word-mode signed integer type so the expansion emits an extsw before
the address-forming add.  When the offset is negative the carry-out
from the low 32 bits cancels the sign-extended upper bits and leaves
the resulting pointer canonical (upper 32 = 0 to match the
zero-extended ABI pointer).

Two-step widen is intentional: a direct convert from sizetype
(unsigned) to a signed word-mode type would zero-extend; we
reinterpret as ssizetype first (no-op at RTL since precisions match),
then widen with sign extension.

--- a/gcc/expr.cc
+++ b/gcc/expr.cc
@@ -9161,6 +9161,42 @@
 	 offset to have matching modes.  */
       else if (TYPE_PRECISION (sizetype) > TYPE_PRECISION (type))
 	treeop1 = fold_convert_loc (loc, type, treeop1);
+      /* When sizetype precision equals pointer precision but the pointer
+	 mode is smaller than the target's natural register word (ELF64 with
+	 ILP32 pointers), the subsequent PLUS_EXPR expansion lowers to a
+	 full-width hardware add against the zero-extended base pointer.
+	 If the offset was produced by signed integer arithmetic, the upper
+	 bits of its 64-bit register form may be non-canonical
+	 (e.g. left as 0xffffffff after a wrapping subtract), and those bits
+	 propagate into the resulting effective address.  Round-trip the
+	 offset through ssizetype (or sizetype for unsigned offsets) so the
+	 expansion emits the required extsw / clrldi canonicalization before
+	 the address-forming add.  */
+      else if (known_lt (GET_MODE_SIZE (TYPE_MODE (type)),
+			 (unsigned int) UNITS_PER_WORD))
+	{
+	  /* Pointer arithmetic uses signed semantics for the offset (a
+	     negative offset means "step backwards"), and on a 64-bit target
+	     with an ILP32 pointer mode the subsequent PLUS_EXPR expansion
+	     lowers to a full-width hardware add.  Sign-widen the offset
+	     through a word-mode signed integer type so the upper bits of
+	     the 64-bit register are canonically sign-extended before the
+	     address-forming add.  When the offset is negative the
+	     carry-out from the low half then cancels the sign-extended
+	     upper bits and leaves the resulting pointer canonical (upper
+	     32 = 0 for a zero-extended ABI pointer base).  */
+	  tree wide_type
+	    = build_nonstandard_integer_type (GET_MODE_PRECISION (word_mode),
+					      /*unsignedp=*/0);
+	  /* Two-step widen: first reinterpret the offset as ssizetype (bit
+	     pattern preserved, no RTL emitted), then sign-extend that to
+	     the word-mode signed type.  Truncating back to `type' leaves
+	     the canonical sign-extension in the 64-bit register.  */
+	  treeop1 = fold_convert_loc (loc, type,
+				      fold_convert_loc (loc, wide_type,
+					fold_convert_loc (loc, ssizetype,
+							  treeop1)));
+	}
       /* FALLTHRU */
 
     case PLUS_EXPR:
